05 Oct 2017 12:57






Dang, I like the idea behind this one (the boots from the saying  being an SCP and combining that with WWI) but the execution is kind of dull.

Wouldn't this work better if the experience delved more into the true horror of WWI? Slowly bleeding out after multiple bayonet stabs is certainly a terrible way to go, but WWI has so much more to offer. Gas weapons, explosive, high calibre automated weapons basically sawing people in half, there's lots you can do.

Now, I'm not saying to make it into a gorefest, but as it stands at the very least the terror experienced by the subject or the colonel who originally owned the boots are far too underplayed. Making the experience more intricate and describing it in greater detail would go a long way towards making this one work.

That being said, right now this will be a -1 for me.







